=== TASK ===
# Host Content Management (Listings CRUD)

## Overview
Build a Host Content Management system for Roam Resort that enables hosts to create, edit, preview, and publish destination listings. Listings include editorial content, image galleries, and experience details. Implement draft/publish visibility controls, validation, autosave drafts, and optimistic UI. Provide a server-side preview endpoint restricted to hosts/admins. Integrate Cloudinary for image uploads and transformations. Ensure robust runtime safety: guard against null/undefined values, use data ?? [] for Supabase-like results, validate API responses, and initialize React state for arrays properly.

Associated pages and flows:
- Host Listing Detail (Read-Only Inquiries): Host-facing read-only view of a listing with related inquiries (no status changes).
- Destination Listings (Browse): Public list of published destinations; leads to Destination Detail pages.
- Destination Detail (Reusable Template): Editorial destination page with in-depth narrative, image gallery, host-sourced content, and CTA to start inquiry flow.

Project context: Roam Resort is an inquiry-based luxury resort platform. Roles include Guest (authenticated), Host (authenticated), and Concierge/Admin. The feature set must align with the V1 scope: listings management, inquiry flow integration, and editorial content experience with a premium design system.

---

## Components to Build

- Listing Editor (Host Dashboard)
  - Create, edit, and preview destination listings.
  - Rich text body (Markdown/Editor), gallery management, metadata, and SEO slug.
  - Status toggle: Draft vs Live.
  - Autosave drafts; optimistic UI during edits.
  - Image upload integration with Cloudinary (direct-to-cloud uploads, transformation URLs).
  - Validation: required title, slug, body length, at least N images, host ownership.
  - Preview endpoint that renders draft content securely (restricted to host/admin).

- Listing Detail View (Host) – Read-Only Inquiries
  - Read-only view of a listing (draft or live) plus a list of related inquiries.
  - No ability to modify inquiries or their status from this view.
  - Display of listing content (title, body, image gallery, metadata) and inquiry metadata (counts, recent activity).

- Destination Listings (Browse) – Public
  - Public list of published (live) listings with teaser content and image thumbnails.
  - Search/filter by destination attributes (tags, location, price range if applicable; for V1 this may be limited).
  - Click into Destination Detail pages.

- Destination Detail (Reusable Template)
  - Editorial, immersive page template used for each listing.
  - In-depth narrative, large hero image(s), image gallery, embedded media, host-sourced content, experiences, and a primary CTA to start inquiry flow.

- API Endpoints & Data Persistence
  - Endpoints for CRUD operations on listings, media, and draft previews.
  - Preview rendering path secured to hosts/admins.
  - Inquiries association retrieval for a listing.

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend

- Tech stack assumptions (adjust to project): React (Function Components), React Router, useState/useEffect, context/auth hooks, and CSS-in-JS or CSS Modules per project conventions.
- State Management: Local component state for forms with optimistic updates; centralize via a listings context/store if applicable.
- UI Components to Build:
  - EditorToolbar, RichTextEditor (Markdown/ProseMirror or equivalent), ImageGalleryUploader (Cloudinary integration), MediaManager (order, captions, alt text), MetadataEditor (tags, location, meta title/description).
  - ListingCard for browse page with hover states, CardGrid for public listings.
  - ListingDetailHostView: read-only view with side panel showing inquiries summary.
  - PreviewModal or PreviewRoute: renders draft content securely.
  - ConfirmationDialog for publish/draft transitions, delete, or discard autosave.
  - Toasts/Snackbars for save status, publish success, validation errors.
  - Form Inputs: title, slug (auto-generated with slugify Web API or front-end), body (markdown), gallery (array of media URLs, public IDs from Cloudinary), metadata fields, publication date (optional), status toggle.
  - Responsive Layout: editorial-friendly grid; hero-first sections; left-aligned content with right-side controls on desktop; mobile-friendly stacking.
- Validation & Safety on UI:
  - Real-time validation: required fields, image count limit (e.g., min 3, max 20), body length, slug uniqueness check via API.
  - Guard all array operations: use (items ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
  - Initialize useState with proper types: useState<Listing[]>([]) for listings lists, useState<ImageAsset[]>([]) for galleries, etc.
  - Safely handle API responses: const dataList = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
  - Optional chaining when accessing nested API results: apiResp?.listing?.title, etc.
- Image Upload & Media:
  - Cloudinary direct-to-cloud upload widget or API flow.
  - Support transformations (max width/height, focal point) via Cloudinary URLs.
  - Maintain media assets as an array with { public_id, url, alt, caption, order }.
- Preview:
  - Secure preview route: /host/listings/:id/preview?token=<secure_token> and/or keep session-scoped authorization.
  - Renders markdown/body with live preview; include gallery viewport.
- Autosave:
  - Debounced autosave (e.g., every 60 seconds or on blur) saving draft state to API or localStorage with versioning.
  - Indicate “Draft autosaved” with timestamp.
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA labels, alt text for images, keyboard navigable controls.
- Performance:
  - Lazy load image galleries, pagination for inquiries in host view.

### Backend

- Tech stack assumptions (adjust to project): Node.js/Express or serverless functions; PostgreSQL; Supabase-like results with data fields; Cloudinary integration; authentication middleware.
- Data Models (PostgreSQL):
  - listings
    - id UUID PK
    - title TEXT NOT NULL
    - slug TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL
    - body TEXT NOT NULL  -- supports Markdown or rich text
    - host_id UUID FK -> hosts(id)
    - status VARCHAR(10) CHECK (status IN ('draft','live')) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'draft'
    - metadata JSONB
    - gallery JSONB  -- array of media assets: [{ public_id, url, alt, caption, order }]
    - created_at TIMESTAMP WITHOUT TIME ZONE DEFAULT now()
    - updated_at TIMESTAMP WITHOUT TIME ZONE DEFAULT now()
    - published_at TIMESTAMP WITHOUT TIME ZONE NULL
  - inquiries
    - id UUID PK
    - listing_id UUID FK -> listings(id)
    - guest_id UUID FK -> guests(id)
    - status VARCHAR(20)  -- e.g., New, InProgress, PendingDeposit, Confirmed
    - message TEXT
    - created_at TIMESTAMP
    - updated_at TIMESTAMP
  - hosts
    - id UUID PK
    - user_id UUID FK -> users(id)
    - ... host profile fields
  - users
    - id UUID PK
    - email TEXT UNIQUE
    - password_hash TEXT
    - role ENUM('guest','host','concierge','admin')
    - ...
- Server-side Validation
  - Validate required fields on create/update: title, slug, body, host_id, at least 1 gallery image for live listings.
  - Validate media limits: max images per listing (e.g., 20).
  - Validate slug uniqueness and slug format.
  - Validate status transitions: cannot move from live to draft without confirmation; restrict via business rules.
- Cloudinary Integration
  - Endpoints or middleware to handle direct uploads from frontend; store public_id and secure_url in gallery items.
  - Transformations support (quality, width, height, crop) via URL parameters.
- Preview Endpoint
  - GET /host/listings/:id/preview
  - Authorization: host member or admin
  - Renders a sanitized, read-only representation of the draft content with markdown rendered.
- Autosave Endpoint
  - POST /host/listings/:id/autosave
  - Persist draft content with a version timestamp; return current draft state.
- API Validation & Safety
  - Use robust null checks; always coerce array results: data ?? [].
  - Guard against null/undefined before mapping arrays.
- Authorization
  - Hosts can CRUD their listings; read-only access to their own inquiries; admins can manage all.
  - Middleware to verify role and ownership.
- Performance & Observability
  - Indexes on listings.slug, listings.host_id, listings.status.
  - Soft delete support if needed (status field toggles, or deleted_at).
  - Logging for create/update/delete with correlation IDs.
- Associated Pages Mapping
  - page_010, page_011, page_012, page_003, page_002 should align with routes and components in frontend.

---

## Integration

- Data Flow
  - Host creates/edits listing via Listing Editor component; on save, send to /host/listings/:id with PATCH/PUT.
  - Autosave hits /host/listings/:id/autosave; response returns updated draft.
  - Preview route consumes draft from backend; user navigates to /host/listings/:id/preview.
  - Public Destination Listings pulls from /listings?status=live to render Destination Listings (Destination Detail uses the same listing data, rendered with the reusable template).
  - Destination Detail uses editorial template to display title, hero gallery, body, experiences, and CTA to initiate inquiry flow.

- Data Consistency and Safety
  - All API responses validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data?.list) ? response.data.list : [].
  - Safely handle optional nested fields via optional chaining.
  - On mapping arrays (gallery, inquiries), guard with (array ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(array) ? array.map(...) : [].

- UI & API Cohesion
  - Frontend must gracefully handle 404/403 for preview, unauthorized edits, and when listing is not found.
  - All forms show real-time validation and inline error messages.
  - Use consistent error messaging and UX patterns for network failures.

---

## User Experience Flow

1. Host logs in and navigates to Host Dashboard > Listings.
2. Create a new listing:
   - Enter title, auto-generate slug (or customize), add body content (markdown), upload image gallery via Cloudinary, add metadata (location, tags).
   - Set status to Draft; autosave kicks in as host types.
   - Click Preview to view draft rendering in a secure preview area.
   - Validate content; on success, switch status to Live (optional confirmation step).
3. Edit existing listing:
   - Modify content; autosave updates draft state in the background.
   - When ready, publish by setting status to Live; updated_at, published_at fields update.
4. Host Listing Detail (Read-Only Inquiries):
   - Open a listing to view editorial content and a list of related inquiries (status read-only).
5. Guests browse Destination Listings (Public):
   - Visit Destination Listings page; see live listings with teaser content.
   - Click into Destination Detail to view in-depth editorial page with narrative and CTAs.
6. Destination Detail (Reusable Template):
   - Scroll through hero image gallery, editorial narrative, host-sourced content, explore experiences, and click CTA to start inquiry flow.

